  "articleSummary": "The article is a tutorial‑style post aimed at developers who maintain personal or small‑scale static blogs and are considering a migration from an older Gatsby setup. It argues that Astro is the most pragmatic choice because its simple API, lack of cloud or framework bias, and strong static‑site features let the author meet strict performance, SEO, and deployment requirements while preserving existing React components, code highlighting, comments, and search. Key points include a brief requirements checklist, a comparison of Astro’s `.astro` files versus client‑side components, and a rundown of the supporting stack (Tailwind, MDX, Pagefind, Utterances, Netlify). The tone is informal yet instructional, using recurring “cornerstone” and “quickly became” metaphors to frame Astro as the central, reliable piece of the upgrade.",
